< text>
Just simply delicious!  I have a thing for the Smoked Chicken Bahn Mi, the yummy Reuben, and Pulled Pork Sandwich.  Every time I stop by, the brisket is sold out!  I can't wait to finally have some sliced brisket. Kids love the Mac n' Cheese.   I like the Potato Salad and spicy Cole Slaw. Excellent IPA on tap.  Well worth a trip out to the coast. Pick up some barbecue and watch the sunset. Or just enjoy a beautiful drive down the coast.  I admit  It doesn't always make it home. It's hard to resist nibbling.</text>

< user_name>
Alex Strickland<//user_name>
<time>1615576850976< /time>< Rating>
4</Rating>
< Text>
*Great Covid Precaution August 2020* - Outdoor seating available: 3 tables in the front and 4 tables in the back (parking lot). Everyone stands in line, one party is allowed to go inside the store at a time. When the food is ready, your number will be called and you pick it up at a separate window. Every employee is wearing a mask.

Shout out to Sydiney, who was busy taping up signs before they opened but still manage to give up some tips and recommendations :)

+Star of the show is the brisket (5 stars). This is coming from a person who almost never likes brisket. The brisket is truly tender, easier cut through with a plastic forks.

+Banh Mi sandwich with ribs (4 stars) - It showed up in burger buns, so I ate it like it was a burger. It had a ton of meat, very satisfying. However, the pickled carrot lacked flavor, maybe the homemade pickles are a better option to make it taste more like a banh mi.

+Sides: Beans & greens (black-eyed peas with collars green and sausage, yum!) and potato salads (strong rosemary fragrance, not your typical one).

-Sausage was good, pulled pork was tender but nothing special, and ribs were not as fatty nor tender and fall-off-the-bone as I expected.

In short, an exciting addition to the BBQ scene, especially in Half Moon Bay. They just opened in April, so come and give it a try.

Tips:
1) Pour the tangy BBQ sauce all over everything
2) You can buy a quarter pound of pulled pork instead of half a pound
3) The line is short (or non-existent) during cold days</Text>

<text>Got a meal to go this Sunday. We got brisket two sides and a chef salad. I‚Äôve traveled the U.S. sampling bbq and breakwater bbq has the best brisket I‚Äôve had. Better than Texas. Better than at st Louis. It was fork cut tender with awesome flavor. The bbq sauce was served on the side and while good frankly I didn‚Äôt use it as the brisket flavor was so awesome. The four sides were Mac and cheese which was spicy and better than almost all others in the area. Dad‚Äôs luncheonette also has an exceptional Mac and cheese but they are both very different. < text>
I didn't have a good experience this year. I usually do. The fired my favorite tax preparer 2 years ago. This was my first year in business as a handyman. I thought the  "tax professionals" would have detailed info on my taxes, the write offs I should be eligible for, and tell me if I missed anything. After all, the promise of getting your maximum refund indicates they know what they are doing. But this "pro" brushed all of my questions off with general dead end statements that clarified nothing. They avoided going into specific details on anything. When I asked her a series of direct questions (like why am I paying $2000.00 on $7000.00 of unemployment, they didn't know anything. They told me "I don't know, I just enter the information in the computer and it does the work for me." I'm certain that there are write offs that I missed. I'm probably going to get audited because they didn't allow me to upload my invoices, or any proofs of income at all besides a 10-99 from a company I did sub-contracting work for. They charged me over $600 and I am done. I have used H&R block for 5 straight years. The "pro" I used should be fired. I'm never going back to this location again.

<resp>{'time': 1545432168247, 'text': 'Thank you! We really appreciate your support and happy you had a good time.'}< /resp>< GmapID>

<date>1545429891419< /date><user_id>115133433254358692432</user_id><user_name>Six O'Nine< /user_name>< Review>
The new renovations in late 2018 really brought this place up to par. It looks basically the same, but the bathrooms are much nicer, the floor is much more level, and the place is just all around cleaner and feels more "solid", while still retaining the distinct, cozy, mountain cabin charm that has always been an intrinsic characteristic of Henflings (aka "Chicken Toss"). Upgrades to the kitchen and bar were welcome and due, and 8ts nice to sit on new, padded, upholstered, swivel barstools.
I went on a "soft open" Wednesday shortly after they reopened, and had a good time playing "Flingo" (Henflings Bingo). Of course, mostly everyone else there knew everyone else, but it wasn't my first time at that rodeo, and both my smile and my cowboy hat seemed well received. And everyone just seemed happy to be back in their local after almost a year closed.
BTW, I have seen some GREAT musical performance at Henfings. The mountains are rife with talented and seasoned musicians, and this is a great, tiny venue to experience them, while practically dancing on their toes and guitar chords.< /Review>

< review>
Usually low prices on gas here, for some odd reason - per the GasBuddy app I use. I like that there's a lot of room for parking at the gas pumps and in front of the store & lots of room for bigger cars like  the Diesel trucks. There's a vacuum station & air station, but I haven't used them yet. It's also easy to get in & out - located on Barstow street where traffic is usually light.

You can pay at pump (accepts debit & credit cards) or pay inside the store. Beware there is a fee for using debit & credit cards inside the store though.

They carry Valero gasoline BTW.

I've had only good experiences here. The clerks are friendly. Lines are short & fast moving. Good selection of quick (or to-go) foods, drinks & candy. Prices are ok - definitely less than 7-Eleven.</review>

<user>113188029045429979763</user><user_name>Dilip Jaju<//user_name><time>1621445618816< /time><Rate>5<//Rate>< review>
I recently refinanced my home with OWNING.COM. When I read recent reviews, I was worried about my decision to refinance with them. Most of the reviews mentioned that their loan is not getting processed for months. After digging into it, I found that the main reason for delay in these cases were due to OWNING.COM merging with GUARANTEED RATE. When I first got in touch with NICK (Nicholas Ramirez) who is a mortgage specialist, I asked this question about delays in processing loans. He assured me that since the merger is completed, my loan will be closed quickly.

After NICK completed my initial application, my file was handed over to Kim H Tran (Loan Processor). From that point onwards it was smooth sailing. Kim was very proactive and was in touch with me throughout the whole process. My loan was closed in record time. I got an excellent rate with no closing cost. There was no surprise at any point. This was the fastest, smoothest and stress free refinancing experience compared to all my previous refinancing experiences. Although I may not need refinancing EVER AGAIN as this may be my last refinance (as advertised by owning.com)due to the excellent rate I got, I would use OWNING.COM without hesitation in future.

NICK and KIM, keep up the excellent job you are doing for your clients. My loan timeline was as follows.

4/30/2021 - Contacted Nick via phone ¬†(He was ready to get details from me on the same day, but I could not do it because of my tight schedule. So I asked him to contact me on 5/2/2021)
5/2/2021 - Nick called me and we completed the application process.
5/3/2021 - Rate locked and file transferred to KIM. Provided him all the documents needed.
5/5/2021 - Minor enquiries from underwriter. I provided the required additional documents the same day.
5/6/2021 - Loan approved.
5/11/2021 - Signed loan papers with Notary.
5/17/2021 - Loan funded.< /review>

< review>
Bottom Line up Front: Owning provided a lower cost loan, at a lower rate, in less than 1/3rd the time Rocket did.

Full Review:

Simply amazed! This captures my reaction at closing, which occurred in just a couple weeks after initial contact. I have been a loyal Rocket Mortgage (3x) customer for too long, and was in week 6 of a refinance with Rocket when I reached out to owning. I had reached a point of frustration in the Rocket Process and my spouse stumbled upon Owning so I conducted some research and gave them a call.

Rocket Frustration:

The frustration with Rocket centered a ‚Äúhard sale‚Äù approach the loan officer had taken combined with the processor communicating vaguely via their application.  The loan officer would dance around loan-origination fees (points) and would always reply with an ‚ÄúI‚Äôm doing the best I can with Credits‚Äù, whenever lender fees were discussed. Her responses consistently lacked clarity and substance.

Owning Experience the Opposite of Rocket:

Owning was 100% transparent in both lender and origination fees. Providing specific answers to justify anywhere from a .25% to 1% point increase. Whereas, Rocket would simply state ‚ÄúThese fees are within Fannie Mae Freddie Mac guidelines‚Äù.  Total closing costs Lender + Origination Fees were 3k less with Owning and there were $0.00 in lender fees.

Owning offered rates that were true to the market whereas Rocket was slightly higher. In my situation, as each refinance/finance is unique, I received a rate from Owning that was a full 1% lower.

Owning was able to close the loan to include escrow funding in less than 3 weeks.

Owning leveraged both technology and old-fashion conversation when needed to work through the finer points of the loan and ensure all expectations were achieved[PW1] . Both Brian and Julie were awesome and a pleasure to work with.

In summary, losing my $500 deposit to Rocket was money well spent.< /review>

<review>I looked into Owning Corporation after hearing about them through word of mouth. I was reasonably skeptical about online lenders at first since I have mainly dealt with large banks such as Chase and BofA. So naturally I had to do more research to put my mind at ease and kept them in check throughout the whole refinancing process. At the end, I was generally happy with my decision to go with them. Here are some of my feedback:
- Loan processing time is pretty fast, compared to big name banks. I sensed that they found a way to streamline the entire process very efficiently. In contrast, I often experienced delays and received redundant requests when dealing with larger banks despite my having all required and verifiable documents.
- John and Kent have been great at following up with my package. John was good at explaining things and Kent was brief and to the point, which I liked. Kent may sound bossy and a bit rude at times but I didn't mind as he was just doing his job.
- I closed with them back in December 2020 but waited until now to give them my feedback because I knew going in that Owning will immediately sell my mortgage to a third party and thus I wanted to capture the entire experience. My mortgage was transferred to Mr. Cooper and I have been generally pleased with them so far.
- I almost stopped my application during the process because Owning was no longer offering competitive rates after initial lockup period on my higher rate has expired. John was ultimately able to offer the lower rate only after I submitted offers from other lenders. It is very important to do your own research in order to get the best rate as possible.

Owning is essentially a service that coordinates lots of independent contractors, like realtors, title companies, notaries, etc, to process loans with a cheaper overhead. The process was really quick - spoke with a loan officer one evening, signed some papers and sent over documentation and signed closing papers within 2 weeks. I compared offers between several other companies and although there was one that was technically better (same interest rate, but more lender credits), I ended up going with Owning because of their promise to close quickly. They were able to waive the appraisal and sent a notary out shortly after, and the load was funded a couple of weeks after that (which was longer than they had expected, but at that point there wasn't much anyone could do). I would have liked my loan processor to be more proactive about updating me about the loan funding timeline, but she did answer all my questions in a timely manner. I did get some surprise fees at the end even though the loan estimate said I would only pay prepaid interest, but it was a only few hundred dollars and ultimately, refinancing is saving me a ton of money as my mortgage rate is now almost cut in half. <Rate>4</Rate>< Text>
Owning Corporation was the company I went with for my first refinance of my first home. My refinance turned out to be more complex than originally thought, in part due to solar loans attached to the property. Despite the complexity and unexpected hiccups, Owning was prompt in their responses and consistently ensured I was not hung out to dry.

The good: Response times were always fast. The employees I worked with were always professional and prompt. All signing that could be done electronically was done so, easing the amount of wet signatures needed on signing days. Documentation was easy to follow. Owning ended up lowering my interest rate as rates continued to slide.

The less-than-good: While everyone I worked with was a pleasure and most unexpected hiccups were dealt with near perfectly, some things fell through the cracks. Had I not doublechecked some of the refinance work after signing, I would have been left paying late penalties on property tax payments. This particular issue may have arisen on Owning or the Title office's behalf, but either way I felt it necessary to dock a star as I was the one to discover the error and did have to contact more than once to get it resolved. However, once the information made it to the proper person, the response was impossibly fast and to my satisfaction.

Overall, I feel most people will have a 5-star experience with Owning and the worst one could expect would be a 4-star. On a personal level, I would likely work with them again for a future refinance.< /Text>

<date>1599610618704< /date><Rate>5</Rate><Review>If this isn't your first rodeo with mortgage and you're a AAA client (great credit, low LTV, organized documents, etc), then Owning is great. When I see these advertisements¬†for such low rates I think there's a catch, but after doing my due diligence I moved forward. I just closed my refinance and got 2.5% with no closing costs and zero issues during the quick process; saving me $380 a month. Insane! NOW, if you're not familiar with the process and need lots of help throughout, or you're not a target client (see below), then this may not be the best route for you. <Text>Overall Myra and Chantha did a great job and get 5 stars, with about a 100 emails from start to finish 9/2020 to 11/2020.  I even had a loan paperwork going with 2 other companies that were not very responsive so I asked Myra and Chantha to match their numbers so I could switch to them and they were able to make that happen.  Owning did well and I would use them again however I have some tips to make it a little more user friendly.  An approximate timeline and the steps could be outlined to help us know what to expect.  The 2 main reasons for the star deduction is the dashboard or lack there of is hard to manage.  Each email had its own link to its own page with documents.  No master list of what was signed or not.  Other lenders have a dashboard that you can easily see that you have submitted everything and signed everything which was very nice, Myra and Chantha kept me on track with emails so not a huge concern but room for improvement.  Also, After signing the loan docs with Notary I thought I was days away from having the loan funded however for whatever reason it was ~3 weeks before funding which left some room for concern that the loan got lost or wouldn't go through. < Review>
My friend did a loan refinance through Owning and referred me to your company. I am extremely grateful Owning was able to help me combine my 1st and 2nd mortgages and even pay off ALL of my credit card debts. I've been waiting over 15 years to do this and Owning is the first Lender/RE Broker that has approved a cash out refinance for me. I have attempted to consolidate my debt multiple times over the years only to be denied each time. I will always be indebted to Owning for giving me a chance and approving my loan.

My Loan Officer, Masa Omura was awesome! He was extremely quick and responsive whenever I reached out to him. I previously worked in the industry and am able to gauge when someone is organized and on top of his duties. His level of customer service and professionalism is top notch! üòä

I loved how fast docs were ready for signing and that we could electronically sign most of the them. The notary that was sent to sign my docs was also great! I don't plan on refinancing in the future, but if I do, I'd happily go through Owning again and I would not hesitate to recommend Owning to my friends!

Another note, due to the COVID-19 situation right now, some parts of your process may be delayed. Knowing this, please be kind to your Loan Officers, Loan Processors, and anyone part of your process. This industry is extremely busy right now and these employees are working extremely hard to help you as the customers. Please be understanding if you don't receive a response right away. I can assure you that if you do contact Owning, you will receive a response if not sooner than later. I can attest that at times the individual that you are communicating with may not be able to help you directly, but they will forward your inquiry to the correct party to resolve your issue.

Once again, I highly recommend Owning and if you choose to go through them, I wish you all the best on your transaction!< /Review>

<text>I had just completed the refinance of our home mortgage in June of 2020, to 2.5%, when I saw a TV commercial for the Owning Corp. advertising 1.75% interest. When I called the previous mortgage company and asked for the lower rate and was turned down as the loan had just funded. I called Owning and they said they would refinance but would have to charge a fee based on the low balance. When they told me the new mortgage payment the savings was only $20 per month. I told them it was not worth my time to complete the paperwork again. Within two weeks I received a call from Owning's Elvis Vuong. I told him I would still be interested but needed to save $100 per moth to be worth my time refinancing again. He was able to secure a new rate of 1.75% with a payment reduction of $88. In the meantime, my mortgage had been sold to CMG Mortgage in San Leandro, CA with one account number and after two months transferred to CMG Mortgage in New Jersey, with a different account number. Now my payment history showed I was delinquent on payments because CMG CA hadn't forwarded the payments to CMG New Jersey. During the time I was attempting to straighten out the payments with CMG, I received delinquent notices, followed by threats of foreclosure. Owning Corp. was understanding and helped with the process finally resolving the matter and completing the refinance. I now have a mortgage under 2%, a rate that will never be seen again. With Owning's help I secured a new loan without an appraisal (based on my home's equity) and as I had recently refinanced I had all the necessary paperwork at hand. Elvis Vuong was easy to contact, listened to my concerns and suggestions and kept me regularly informed on the progress of the loan. I would highly recommend doing business with Owning and Elvis Vuong.<//text><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< response>

<rating>4<//rating><Text>The great thing about refinancing through Owning was the speed of the re-fi.  It took two weeks from beginning to end, the fastest I have ever done a re-fi.  everything went exactly as promised, no hidden fees or problems.  My initial contact Brandon was courteous and professional on the phone.  My loan processor Edgar always responded quickly to my emails even if it was late at night.
So why not 5 stars?  Two reasons.  The escrow company used by Owning is Lenders Choice Escrow.  It was disclosed in the documents I signed at closing that Lenders Choice Escrow is owned or affiliated with Owning.com.  I think that escrow companies should be independent third parties separate from lender or borrower.  Second reason: It was sometimes hard to get the people at Owning on the phone for a voice conversation...although as I have said above my emails were always responded to promptly.
Summary:  Would I recommend Owning.com?  Yes, definitely.  I have already recommended them to some of my friends.  Overall, I was very happy with my experience.< /Text><Pictures>None< /Pictures><resp>None<//resp>< gmap_id>

<Name>Dennis Ju</Name>< Time>
1597000464869</Time>
<rate>4<//rate><Review>I refinanced my mortgage with Owning after shopping around with other services like Better. Owning's rates and closing costs (or lack thereof) were significantly better than the competition. Better even has a price guarantee, but they still couldn't meet or beat Better's rates.

I also like how simple Owning's pricing structure is. There's just one rate, no closing costs, and it's clearly displayed on the homepage. However, I can see how this lack of options can be problematic for those looking to cash-out refi or secure jumbo loans.

Their service was excellent. Owning was in regular communication with me to make sure the refi process was moving along smoothly. The time to closing the refinance was also very quick, approximately three weeks from the day I submitted my application.

The main drawback of Owning is their lack of digital tooling, likely due to being a relatively new company. Digital competitors like Better are light years ahead in providing online services. Owning's application is done via PDF attachments sent over email. They have a way's to go in leveraging online forms, digital signatures, online application status, and other self-service tools. I imagine they'll add these features as the company grows.

A couple minor quibbles. One, an Owning rep kept pestering me to write an online review. I told them I wanted to wait until I saw confirmation that my previous mortgage was paid off, but she continued to send me emails. The rep even had the audacity to send me a canned positive review to "copy and paste" on Google Reviews. Not classy at all.

Secondly, since they paid the first installment for the new mortgage, I sent my first payment to Owning via check (no online payments). A few weeks later, they called asking if I had sent payment, and I indicated yes. They waited a few days then said they hadn't received payment and requested I re-send payment, which I did. A few days later, they cashed my first check which I sent weeks ago. I had to stop payment on the second check I mailed. This wasn't a big deal, but easily avoidable if they had online payments with email confirmations.

I'm giving Owning four stars. I'd happily recommend them to others. To stay competitive with this new wave of online real estate tech, they need to build out their digital tools, but they're on the right track.< /Review><pics>None< /pics>< Response>
{'time': 1597098580597, 'text': "Hi Dennis, thanks so much for your thoughtful feedback! We're glad you were pleased with Owning's rates and timetable, and we will definitely continue to improve our customer tools and service going forward. We'll take your feedback into account, thanks again and enjoy your savings!"}</Response>

< Text>
I like staff who are knowledgeable, do not push sales, provide straight forward information, like their job, and believe that their customers are not dumb. I found all these qualities in Jeff Johnson who helped me start the loan process.  I had talked to Jeff six months ago and our conversation was just like talking to a friend and he gave me good advice regarding my loans. < review>
I would have loved to of given this company a five star rating. Unfortunately they have policies that they have in place and follow but do not make available for their customers to see. I recently finished my refi and it went fairly smoothly and in the timely manner that they said it would. Problem is a few weeks later interest rates dropped even lower. I asked if I could refi again and they said they have a policy they will not do another refi within 12 months. I asked if I could see the documentation that I signed stating that. They said I did not and that it was just a policy that their company follows. The problem is I did not know this policy upfront. They do not disclose that to you upfront.
They told me they would have told me their policies on that if I would have asked. The problem is how are you supposed to know questions to policies that you don‚Äôt even know exist. I gave them the opportunity to try and make it right and square it up and maybe put their policies in writing for customers in the future. They did not want hear anything to do with that. Consequently I had three friends that were in the beginning process that now are backed out and five customers that were planning on reaching out to this company. It does seem very shady afterwards that there is policies in place that they do not disclose but yet you were supposed to know to ask these questions.

To be honest in the future I will probably choose a different company. It‚Äôs a shame that companies are still playing games like this after all of the housing market crisis and now this COVID-19.
I would love to go back and change my rating at a different date if they decide to change their policies and make their policies public. After the hundreds of pages you sign for a refinance you would think it would be something they would disclose.< /review>

< Text>
I decided to refinance a rental with a cash out on January 27, 2020.  Owning Company was recommended by a friend who  just refinanced his home, with Owning Company.  He spoke highly of the company and of their efficiency.  He provided me with their Processor's Name, David Moc, and a contact Telephone number.

I contacted Mr. Moc that afternoon by telephone and was immediately impressed by his professionalism, courtesy and genuine desire to be helpful.  We started the loan process and he provided me with a list of documents his company  would require.  On the morning of January 28, 2020,  I had provided Mr. Moc with the documents he requested, and my credit check was completed.  Mr. Moc had an appraiser contact me that afternoon and an appraisal was scheduled and completed on January 29, 2020.

Mr. Moc then assigned my Loan to, Processor  Mr. Martin Bui, another exemplary professional.  On January 31, 2020, Mr. Bui informed me that my loan was complete and asked if I could sign loan Documents on February 4, 2020, with a closing set for February 10, 2020.

I was out of town, and ended up signing on February 7, 2020.  The loan closed and was funded on February 12, 2020.  In short I have financed a number of properties through the years and this was by far the best mortgage/finance/refinance experience I have ever had.  Mr. Moc and Mr. Bui are both exceptional individuals and their efforts make Owning Company an industry leader.  I highly recommend this company and their employees.< /Text>

One day I was driving to work when I heard the radio ad for Owning, and their no closing cost refinance. I figured what have I got to lose, and called them. I met John Nguyen, who offered me an incredibly low rate and no PMI. Shortly after signing initial disclosures, my current lender NEWREZ found out I was going to refinance with another lender and called me. < Review>
With all the marketing hype in the mass media, I was skeptical at first in Owning's ability to deliver as advertised.   With a couple (complex with Income-to-loan ratio for multiple rentals) re-financing already attempted, there was this and that, then the Appraisal. This re-fi could have also fallen apart, if not for the loan officer's Hai's persistence, can-do attitude and Let's see what we can do....  that saved the loan.  He works within the system, and knows his stuff well as a real estate broker.  As a salesman he is not afraid to have the door slammed in his face.  He would call when my phone didn't work.  He would call late in the day, .... over and again, i.e. whatever it takes.  He did not give up on me.  If this is Professionalism, Hai's got it.  I hope others out there who Hai can help would not hesitate to give him a chance.  He has worked hard to earn his Success.  By the time the loan was funded, he and his tea</Review>
